column5: today was a great day me and the cuzin caught more then you can shake a stick at!! heres some big and nice ones from today!!         may your float be happy and under the water muddy
nice job fellers ... what a day !!! HUSH HUSH!
dam lampreys are having a freaking feast on these fish every single fish had eel marks on it.
Great photos, muddywater.  Hella report, thx.
Spectacular pics there guys.  Great report.  Joey
Looks like a great day indeed!  Nice pics - thanks for sharing.  So, your cousin uses a mitchell 300 eh?  An oldie, but a goodie.  Were they mostly caught on roe?  I know one of 'em was...
nice fish,congrats on a great day
Love that saying!  Great job out there....awesome looking fish!
Some nice trout there!  Good job!
Liven the dream boys, good job
NICE, VERY NICE.......its rare to see those mitchells still in action !!!

thats my garcia mitchell 308 very hard to find these days but i love the sound of the drag on them !!. i have to replace my washers alot which are made from margarine containers and when big fish run they warp and melt
